%U A396858 2362432090396,5406419688825,11728663718656,24276802571785,48202690758300,92223585791011,170669877386800
%N A396858 The number of n-colorings of the faces of the pyritohedron up to rotation and reflection.
%C A396858 A pyritohedron has 12 pentagonal faces and 20 vertices and is topologically equivalent to a dodecahedron.
%C A396858 Colorings are counted up to the pyritohedral symmetry group of order 24.
%H A396858 Peter Kagey and William Keehn, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.26140">Escher's Cubes: Tiling the Faces of Polyhedra</a>, arXiv:2606.26140 [math.GM], 2026. See pp. 5, 10.
%H A396858 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetrahedral_symmetry#Pyritohedral_symmetry">Pyritohedral symmetry</a>.
%H A396858 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dodecahedron#Pyritohedron">Pyritohedron</a>.
%F A396858 a(n) = (n^12 + 3*n^8 + 8*n^2 + 8*n^4 + 4*n^6)/24.
%t A396858 A396858[n_] := (n^12 + 3 n^4 n^4 + 8 n^2 + 8 n^4 + 4 n^6)/24
%Y A396858 Cf. A128766 (octahedron), A199406 (rhombic dodecahedron), A252704 (icosahedron), A252705 (dodecahedron), A274900 (rhombicuboctahedron), A337963 (rhombic triacontahedron), A378473 (tetrakis hexahedron), A378474 (disdyakis dodecahedron), A378475 (pentagonal icositetrahedron), A378476 (triakis icosahedron), A378477 (disdyakis triacontahedron), A378478 (pentagonal hexecontahedron).
%K A396858 nonn,changed
%O A396858 0,3
